-- Microsoft May Get EU Fine This Week on Browser Choice, MLex Says
-- B y   A o i f e   W h i t e
-- 2013-03-04T16:51:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-04/microsoft-may-get-eu-fine-this-week-on-browser-choice-mlex-says.html
Microsoft Corp. (MSFT)  may be fined by
European Union regulators as soon as March 6 for violating a
settlement to give users a choice of web browsers, MLex reported
today without saying where it got the information.  Antoine Colombani, a spokesman for the European Commission,
declined to comment on the report. EU Competition Commissioner
Joaquin Almunia will hold a press conference on Wednesday on an
unspecified matter, he said.  Robin Koch, a spokesman for Microsoft, declined to comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aoife White in Brussels at 
 awhite62@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
